&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span&gt;Job Title: Highly Specialist Occupational Therapist&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Band: &lt;/strong&gt;7&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Hours: &lt;/strong&gt; 15 hours &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; We have an exciting opportunity for a dynamic Occupational Therapist who would like to work with patients receiving palliative care and patients with long term health conditions, to join our multi-professional hospital palliative care team in Surrey. This post will work alongside the ward teams to support patients with specialist palliative care needs. It is the vision of the team to develop the service further, linking closely with hospice and charity teams, providing an invaluable link between the services. There is potential to expand the service and develop the role further.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; The successful applicant will demonstrate excellent communication skills in supporting ward teams to care for patients with palliative care needs; carrying out specialist assessments; assisting with complex end of life discharges; liaising with a wide range of healthcare professionals and clearly documenting clinical advice. We are looking for candidates who display strong leadership qualities and who are able to act as a role-model to staff across the Trust. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;span&gt;We are looking for someone who is motivated to contribute, facilitate, design and lead service developments, innovations and audit within the Supportive and Palliative care team at Ashford and St Peter’s hospital. &lt;/span&gt;A strong commitment to education and teaching is also important.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The Trust is committed to providing training and education to support the development of its staff. You will be supported to develop your clinical and leadership skills through formal supervision and appraisal. There will also be internal and external training opportunities.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Palliative or End of Life Care experience is essential, as is recent experience of working in a leadership role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &lt;span&gt;Ashford and St Peter’s offers a seven day service across some specialities and you will be expected to support this on a rota system.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Access to a car and a full UK driving licence is required for this role&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;There is a hospital hopper bus service which operates frequently throughout the day between Ashford and St Peter’s Hospital sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt; &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For further information please contact Isla Green clinical lead for therapies- Respiratory &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Isla.green@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Or Susan Dargan Team lead- Supportive and Palliative care &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Susan.dargan@nhs.net&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
